title.narrative: Timeliness. Improvements in the timeliness of key statistics as evidenced by reducing the time lag in the publication of annual labor force estimates
Coherence. An improvement in the coherence of BPS statistics as evidenced by a reduction in the discrepancy between the sum of theProvincial estimates of GDRP and the GDP for Indonesia
Accuracy. Demonstrable improvement in the accuracy of key statistics, as evidenced by: (b) an increase in the user satisfaction with the accuracy of BPS statistics
Accessibility. An improvement in the accessibility of BPS statistics as evidenced by: (a) a dynamic up-to-date web site
Accuracy. Demonstrable improvement in the accuracy of key statistics as evidenced by: (a) an increase in the response rate of the Annual Survey of large and medium manufacturing businesses
Accessibility. An improvement in the accessibility of BPS statistics as evidenced by: (b) an increase in the user satisfaction with the accessibility of BPS statistics
An effective, integrated performance management system for BPS

baseline.value: A performance system that is not in line with BPS's future strategic direction and does not provide sufficient incentive forimproved performance

target.value: An effective Performance Management System for BPS

actual.value: BPS-wide Strategy Map completed. KPIs using Balanced Scorecard for Echelon I and II are completed, but not yet endorsed by BPSExecutives

title.narrative: Improved alignment of the BPS organization and the future work environment

baseline.value: BPS organization alignment is not yet optimal

target.value: Improvement of the organizational design based on the initial experience and feedback from internal stakeholders

actual.value: Macro-Level Organization Structure (Echelon I and II) based on Generic Statistical Business Process Model (GSBPM) is completed, butnot yet endorsed by BPS Executives

title.narrative: Improvement in ICT Governance and Management

baseline.value: ICT Strategy in BPS Strategic Plan 2009-2014; Existing ICT functions in the Regulation of the Head of BPS No.1/2009 on BPSOrganization; Initial business process mapping and analysis in BPS Analysis Document 2010-2011

target.value: Improvement of ICT Strategy, and ICT Governance & Management Framework based on the initial experience and feedback from internalstakeholders

actual.value: IT Strategy, Enterprise Architecture (EA) and IT Transformation Roadmap have been finalized and agreed by BPS Executives. SOPs forIT Services Management have been prepared.

title.narrative: The establishment of a Common Business Register (BR) and a Large Business Unit (LBU)

target.value: Review of effectiveness of BR maintenance strategy

actual.value: Detailed Design Document for the Statistical Business Register is in finalization phase.

title.narrative: A Human Resource that is aligned with BPS's future strategic direction

baseline.value: No HR Strategic Plan is available; No Technical and Non-Technical Competency Framework and Dictionary are available

target.value: Improvement of BPS HR Strategic Plan based on the initial experience and feedback from internal stakeholders; Implementati on ofimproved HR Strategic Plan

actual.value: Review of current BPS capability, tools and regulations completed, including core & managerial competencies, workload analysis,regulation review, training & development strategy. Draft core & managerial competencies for future BPS completed, but not yetendorsed by BPS Executives.

title.narrative: The successful implementation of a Quality Assurance Framework across BPS

baseline.value: No corporate quality assurance policy or program

target.value: Quality assurance program established and effective

actual.value: Quality governance structure has been discussed and may be established in 2017; study of quality gates conducted for Large andMedium Manufacturing Industries Statistics.

baseline.value: No corporately agreed project management system

target.value: Review of the application of the BPS Project Management System

actual.value: 227 BPS managers have been trained in project management

title.narrative: Availability of an integrated data and information service system supported by the data warehouse

baseline.value: No integrated data & information system supported by data warehouse available

actual.value: Enterprise Architecture (EA) and Statistical Business Framework and Architecture (SBFA) have been finalized and agreed by BPSExecutives. Detailed Design Documents for the working survey databases, input and dissemination data warehouses are in finalizationphase.

title.narrative: Interpretability. An improvement in the interpretability of BPS statistics as evidenced by an increase in the statistics produced by BPS that have supporting meta data

baseline.value: No statistics with fully documented metadata

actual.value: 309 datasets with metadata information published in BPS Microdata Catalog System

title.narrative: Relevance. Availability of important new statistics as evidenced by establishment of a national producer price index

baseline.value: PPI available for agricultural sector, excluding forestry sub-sector

target.value: PPI available for all provinces and most large districts

actual.value: National PPI published for the following additional sectors: Passenger Transportation Services, Electricity and Gas Supply, andWater Supply. Study conducted for the following additional sectors: Freight Transportation, Telecommunications, and FinanceServices. Preparation for Provincial PPI has been conducted with construction of weights for 3 sectors in 5 provinces.

title.narrative: Development of application systems for statistical production and dissemination

baseline.value: Systems for common statistical infrastructure do not exist; Statistical processing systems developed by SIS and subject matterareas available

target.value: Application systems for all statistical infrastructure available and in use

actual.value: Detailed Design Documents for Corporate Statistical Infrastructure (CSIs) are in finalization phase
